alert_notes.note:
Janzen called back after crank sensor was installed saying the water pump was also leaking. I said that they never mentioned anything of the sort and ask if the customer complained of a leak. Shop said they noticed the leak and asked the  customer if they should look further. He apparently agreed. I asked for pictures and rec'd 4 that showed nothing. I replied such. I rec'd another picture with circles that showed some dried residue of some sort. I told the shop to send the trick to OK Tire Steinbach for a second opinion.
The shop called me asking why they have to send it elsewhere and that the customer didn't want to go there. I explained the underwriters wanted the second opinion and that we would not entertain the claim without the second opinion. The shop then said, "Well, it's not a live leak but you can see where it did leak at one time." WOW! The residue could have been from someone spilling some sort of liquid months or years ago. A.H.
